MALAYSIA DAYBOOK: PLUS Takeover Vote, January Inflation Data

-- B y   B a r r y   P o r t e r
-- 
2011-02-22T21:39:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/malaysia-daybook-plus-takeover-vote-january-inflation-data.html
PLUS Expressways Bhd.,  Malaysia ’s
biggest toll-road operator, will ask its shareholders to vote on
a proposed 23 billion-ringgit ($7.5 billion) takeover offer by
UEM Group Bhd. and the Employees Provident Fund.  An extraordinary meeting will be held at 11 a.m. in Selangor
today. The company is also expected to announce fourth-quarter
earnings.  WHAT TO WATCH:
* Consumer price inflation likely rose 2.4 percent in January,
according to the median forecast of 15 economists surveyed by
Bloomberg News. The government will announce data at 5 p.m.
* Axiata Group Bhd. (AXIATA MK) will announce second-quarter
earnings after 12:30 p.m.
* Kuala Lumpur Kepong Bhd. (KLK MK) is expected to announce
first-quarter earnings after 5 p.m.  MARKETS:
* Malaysia’s FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI Index fell 0.8 percent.
* The MSCI Asia Pacific Index dropped 1.8 percent.
* The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  lost 1.4 percent.
* Palm oil May-delivery futures advanced 0.4 percent to 3,669
ringgit ($1,202) a metric ton.  EQUITY PREVIEW:
* British American Tobacco (Malaysia) Bhd. (ROTH MK): Malaysia’s
biggest cigarette-maker said fourth-quarter net income rose 5.7
percent from a year earlier to 182.7 million ringgit as gains
from asset sales countered a drop in revenue.
* Genting Bhd. (GENT MK): Genting Singapore Plc, the group’s
51.7 percent-owned Singapore casino resort unit, said its net
loss widened in the fourth quarter to S$150.3 million ($117
million).
* Genting Plantations Bhd. (GENP MK): The palm oil producer said
fourth-quarter net income rose 31 percent to 102.7 million
ringgit after fetching higher prices for its edible oil. It
declared a special dividend of 3 sen a share, in addition to a
5.5 sen final dividend.
* MMC Corp. (MMC MK): The ports, power and construction group
backed by billionaire Syed Mokhtar Al-Bukhary said fourth-
quarter profit slipped 3.7 percent to 104.6 ringgit on higher
operating expenses and finance costs.
* Petronas Gas Bhd. (PTG MK): The Malaysian natural gas
distributor said third-quarter net income jumped 50.4 percent to
400.7 million ringgit on higher gas processing and gas
transportation revenue.
* Tanco Holdings Bhd. (TANC MK): The Malaysian property manager
and developer agreed to settle outstanding credit facilities
with Lehman Brothers Commercial Corp. Asia Ltd., which is in
liquidation. The Kuala Lumpur-based company will pay Lehman 44
million ringgit in cash and transfer properties valued at 100.6
million ringgit, according to an exchange filing.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Barry Porter in  Kuala Lumpur  at 
